ïíŸ@048760802e8cf7d98684bf2d9d0f1ad56a0d6c6775dc49c3ff38fcb0dd31af48⁄ÝTitle: This week in Nushell #244
Path: Nushell
Content:
devyn 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12675] fixed inconsistent print behavior
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12673] added a bit more delay before 
``ps``
 calls in plugin persistence tests
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12670] added plugin error propagation on write/flush
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12664] introduced Msgpack commands
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12646] further improved messages related to error propagation on plugin calls
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12639] accepted filenames in other plugin management commands
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12634] renamed plugin cache file to plugin registry file
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12633] fixed (and tested) a deadlock that can happen while waiting for protocol info
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12632] fixed error message propagation on plugin call failure
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12626] added 
``ErrSpan``
 extension trait for 
``Result``
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12613] updated 
``toolkit register plugins``
 to 
``toolkit add plugins``
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12612] made 
``stress_internals``
 exit(1) on IO error
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12607] deprecated 
``register``
 and added 
``plugin use``
, and 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12579] overhauled the plugin cache file with a new msgpack+brotli format
.
IanManske 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12668] fixed an 
``into bits``
 example
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12667] added a deprecation warning to 
``describe --collect-lazyrecords``
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12666] fixed 
``each``
 signature
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12659] removed deprecated flags on 
``run-external``
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12658] removed deprecated flags on 
``commandline``
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12656] deprecated lazy records
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12648] made exit code available in 
``catch``
 block
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12619] improved the "input and output are the same file" error text
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12610] shrunk the size of 
``Expr``
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12609] cleaned up 
``nu-cmd-lang``
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12601] made the same file error more likely to appear
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12582] removed the 
``Value::Block``
 case
, and 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12541] refactored using 
``ClosureEval``
 types
.
hustcer 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12681] upgraded CI to fix macOS arm64 build errors
.
merelymyself 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12672] made 
``grid``
 throw an error when not enough columns are provided
.
WindSoilder 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12491] avoided panic when piping a variable to a custom command which has recursive calls
.
KAAtheWiseGit 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12665] fixed example wording in 
``seq date``
.
fdncred updated to the latest reedline twice (
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12644] 1
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12630] 2
)
stormasm 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12621] bumped reedline
.
amtoine 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12608] fixed a typo in the documentation of 
``nuon::ToStyle``
.
sholderbach 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12606] updated 
``ratatui``
 to deduplicate 
``syn``
 in build
 and 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12604] did a small refactor in 
``cal``
.
maxim-uvarov 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12600] added search_term "str extract" to 
``parse``
 command
.
ayax79 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12576] added commands for working with the plugin cache
.
íŸ@a759d711356f24e2910e3155869965683def79bd807da8b5d21592b5e176afcfŸ€Title: This week in Nushell #244
Path: Extension
Content:
AucaCoyan 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/vscode-nushell-lang/pull/182] added support for 
``def 'my-function'``
 syntax highlighting and added tests to it
.
íŸ@0d2ef0456e06dbb027bb6fc724dd2414bc17aaaf522ef6aa26139d73c9677438⁄ÓTitle: This week in Nushell #244
Path: Documentation
Content:
isti115 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell.github.io/pull/1369] updated docs for commands from 
``nu-std/std/dirs.nu``
 and provided a 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell.github.io/pull/1370] fixup for it
.
IanManske 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell.github.io/pull/1366] fixed broken links
 and 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell.github.io/pull/1352] updated docs for 0.92.0 (file, pipes, and io)
.
íŸ@813a9231f9e70c84d4fc9678e0a880a620240e881d0d19227cf552753b252bc0⁄Title: This week in Nushell #244
Path: Nu_Scripts
Content:
zhangymPerson 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nu_scripts/pull/824] added a git worktree command
.
godrja 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nu_scripts/pull/823] made Winget custom completions fixes
.
sholderbach 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nu_scripts/pull/814] added 
``nu_plugin_polars``
 as a crate to release
.
íŸ@e8f11a5732854a3da3c5888e80f5b016907443cb38b350803bec25402e3ed995⁄˝Title: This week in Nushell #244
Path: reedline
Content:
sholderbach 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/reedline/pull/784] removed debug print
.
sigoden 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/reedline/pull/783] fixed unexpected spaces after large buffer input
.
maxomatic458 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/reedline/pull/781] fixed ide menu not reporting correct required_lines
.
bew 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/reedline/pull/770] properly fixed the logic around prompt re-use & Host Command handling
.
